modules.name: AWS.Shield
modules.comments:
AWS Shield Advanced

This is the AWS Shield Advanced API Reference. This guide is for developers who need detailed information about the AWS Shield Advanced API actions, data types, and errors. For detailed information about AWS WAF and AWS Shield Advanced features and an overview of how to use the AWS WAF and AWS Shield Advanced APIs, see the AWS WAF and AWS Shield Developer Guide.

declarations.comments: Enables AWS Shield Advanced for a specific AWS resource. The resource can be an Amazon CloudFront distribution, Elastic Load Balancing load balancer, Elastic IP Address, or an Amazon Route 53 hosted zone.
declarations.title: createProtection

declarations.comments: Activates AWS Shield Advanced for an account.
declarations.title: createSubscription

declarations.comments: Deletes an AWS Shield Advanced Protection.
declarations.title: deleteProtection

declarations.comments: Removes AWS Shield Advanced from an account. AWS Shield Advanced requires a 1-year subscription commitment. You cannot delete a subscription prior to the completion of that commitment.
declarations.title: deleteSubscription

declarations.comments: Describes the details of a DDoS attack.
declarations.title: describeAttack

declarations.comments: Lists the details of a Protection object.
declarations.title: describeProtection

declarations.comments: Provides details about the AWS Shield Advanced subscription for an account.
declarations.title: describeSubscription

declarations.comments: Returns the SubscriptionState, either Active or Inactive.
declarations.title: getSubscriptionState

declarations.comments: Returns all ongoing DDoS attacks or all DDoS attacks during a specified time period.
declarations.title: listAttacks

declarations.comments: Lists all Protection objects for the account.
declarations.title: listProtections

declarations.comments: The details of a DDoS attack.
declarations.title: AttackDetail

declarations.comments: Details of the described attack.
declarations.title: AttackProperty

declarations.comments: Summarizes all DDoS attacks for a specified time period.
declarations.title: AttackSummary

declarations.comments: Describes the attack.
declarations.title: AttackVectorDescription

declarations.comments: A contributor to the attack and their contribution.
declarations.title: Contributor

declarations.comments: Exception that indicates that a problem occurred with the service infrastructure. You can retry the request.
declarations.title: InternalErrorException

declarations.comments: Exception that indicates that the operation would not cause any change to occur.
declarations.title: InvalidOperationException

declarations.comments: Exception that indicates that the parameters passed to the API are invalid.
declarations.title: InvalidParameterException

declarations.comments: Exception that indicates that the resource is invalid. You might not have access to the resource, or the resource might not exist.
declarations.title: InvalidResourceException

declarations.comments:
Exception that indicates that the operation would exceed a limit.

Type is the type of limit that would be exceeded.

Limit is the threshold that would be exceeded.
declarations.title: LimitsExceededException

declarations.comments: Exception that indicates that the subscription you are trying to delete has not yet completed the 1-year commitment. You cannot delete this subscription.
declarations.title: LockedSubscriptionException

declarations.comments: The mitigation applied to a DDoS attack.
declarations.title: Mitigation

declarations.comments: Exception that indicates that the protection state has been modified by another client. You can retry the request.
declarations.title: OptimisticLockException

declarations.comments: An object that represents a resource that is under DDoS protection.
declarations.title: Protection

declarations.comments: Exception indicating the specified resource already exists.
declarations.title: ResourceAlreadyExistsException

declarations.comments: Exception indicating the specified resource does not exist.
declarations.title: ResourceNotFoundException

declarations.comments: The attack information for the specified SubResource.
declarations.title: SubResourceSummary

declarations.comments: Information about the AWS Shield Advanced subscription for an account.
declarations.title: Subscription

declarations.comments: A summary of information about the attack.
declarations.title: SummarizedAttackVector

declarations.comments: The counter that describes a DDoS attack.
declarations.title: SummarizedCounter

declarations.comments: The time range.
declarations.title: TimeRange
